    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking into some stuff for a project in SE Portland. Can you explain how mixed-use zoning usually applies to residential districts? specifically if we're talking about small scale commercial like a corner grocery, what are the main things to look out for regarding setbacks and building encroachment on the property line?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In mixed-use residential districts, zoning allows for small-scale commercial uses like a corner grocery integrated near housing. Key things to check are the specific zoning ordinance regarding allowable uses within residential zones and any size limits for the commercial component. For setbacks and encroachments, look for requirements dictating the distance buildings must be from property lines, which often differ between residential and commercial structures to ensure light and air. Pay close attention to rules about parking requirements and impervious surface coverage as well.",
      "source": "target",
