    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I'm particularly worried about the encroachment part though. If the building footprint ends up being slightly over the line or if there's some kind of violation with the boundary, what's the typical process for addressing those unauthorized encroachments? How does the city usually handle folks who just cross those lines?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The typical process starts with the city issuing a Notice of Violation after an inspection reveals the encroachment. This notice usually gives the property owner a specific timeframe to correct the issue, such as removing the portion of the structure that crosses the line. If the owner fails to comply, the city can take enforcement actions, which may involve fines or, in severe cases, legal action to compel removal. It is always best to proactively consult with SE Portland's planning department before construction to prevent any violations.",
      "source": "target",
